data.title: Events
data.meta_description: With engaging events, compelling lectures, and skill-building workshops, the Penn Libraries is a hub for cultural and educational activity at the University of Pennsylvania. Many library events and exhibitions are open to the public.
data.text:
Aug 28

Workshop

Open to Penn Students, Faculty, and Staff

R Basics: Get Started in RStudio

Never worked in R? Get a jump on your business or academic career by exploring this powerful statistical programming language and its popular environment, RStudio.

August 28, 2024

12:00pm - 1:30pm

Hybrid: Virtual and in-person at Yablon Financial Resources Lab, Room 244, Van Pelt-Dietrich Library Center

Aug 29

Workshop

Open to Penn Students, Faculty, and Staff

Excel Basics: Get Started

Never used Excel? Get ready for course and job assignments by learning how Microsoft Excel organizes data and by preparing tables for analysis.

August 29, 2024

12:00pm - 1:15pm

Hybrid: Virtual and in-person at Yablon Financial Resources Lab, Room 244, Van Pelt-Dietrich Library Center

Aug 30

Workshop

Open to the Public

Postcards to Home: An Open Studio Printing Event

Stop by the Weitzman Plaza and use the Common Press portable printing press to letterpress-print postcards with a greeting from Penn.

August 30, 2024

1:00pm - 4:00pm

Weitzman Plaza

Sep 03

Workshop

Open to the Public

Copyright Basics

Review the basics of U.S. copyright law with the Libraries' dedicated copyright advisor, Stephen Wolfson.

September 3, 2024

11:00am - 12:00pm

Meyerson Conference Room, Van Pelt-Dietrich Library Center, Second Floor

Sep 03

Workshop

Open to Penn Students, Faculty, and Staff

Tea & Tarot -- Beginning of Classes Edition

Come to Tea & Tarot where you can learn what the fall semester has in store for you (insert ominous laugh)!

September 3, 2024

12:00pm - 1:00pm

Weigle Information Commons, Van Pelt-Dietrich Center, 1st floor

Sep 03

Workshop

Open to Penn Students, Faculty, and Staff

History of Type and Letterpress Printing with guided tour and demonstration

A guided tour and demonstration of letterpress printing and typography, including the history of letterpress printing, type and books from 1000 CE to now, as well as demonstrations of how movable type is used and the mechanical history of all the different presses at Common Press.

This is not the studio use orientation.

September 3, 2024

12:00pm - 1:00pm

Common Press

Sep 03

Workshop

Open to Penn Students, Faculty, and Staff

SQL Basics: Get Tables Into and Out of a Database​

Have database files to merge and extract for analysis? With this session, you'll be able to get the files you need, in a useable format, quickly via the lightweight DB Browser for SQLite.

September 3, 2024

12:00pm - 1:15pm

Hybrid: Virtual and in-person at Yablon Financial Resources Lab, Room 244, Van Pelt-Dietrich Library Center

Sep 03

Workshop

Open to Penn Students, Faculty, and Staff

Introduction to QGIS

Learn how to create, edit, and manage geospatial data using QGIS, including adding data from different sources, performing data analysis, and using various data management tools.

September 3, 2024

4:00pm - 5:00pm

Research Data and Digital Scholarship Exchange (RDDSx), Van Pelt-Dietrich Library Center, First Floor

Sep 04

Workshop

Open to Penn Students, Faculty, and Staff

R Basics: Prepare Data for Modeling and Analysis​

Eager to analyze data? This hands-on experience will help you organize and format finance data, supporting your modeling or machine learning workflow.

September 4, 2024

12:00pm - 1:30pm

Hybrid: Virtual and in-person at Yablon Financial Resources Lab, Room 244, Van Pelt-Dietrich Library Center
